<TEXT>
a small earthquake shook part of the suburban 
san fernando valley on wednesday authorities said 
the 343 pm quake measured 31 on the richter scale and was 
centered five miles southwest of van nuys said robert finn 
spokesman for the california institute of technology in pasadena 
another little quake measuring 26 was recorded at 1201 pm 
and was centered 10 miles northwest of palm springs finn said 
it was too small to determine if it was on the san andreas fault 
which runs through the north palm springs area he said there were 
no reports of damage or injury 
quakes of such magnitude usually dont cause damage in california 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale of ground motion can 
cause slight damage locally 4 moderate damage 5 considerable 
damage 6 severe damage a 7 reading is a major earthquake 
capable of widespread heavy damage 8 is a great quake capable 
of tremendous damage 
</TEXT>
