<TEXT>
the italian news agency ansa has suspended its 
transmissions because of a labor dispute with its teletype operators 
over plans to have journalists transmit the news directly from 
computer terminals 
ansa management said the agency shut down wednesday night after 
teletype operators began transmitting only press releases and not 
news written by agency journalists there was no immediate word on 
when service would resume 
an ansa source who asked not to be identified said the teletype 
workers have staged a work slowdown for several weeks to protest the 
computerization plans 
the source said the agency had planned to allow journalists to 
begin transmitting news on its french english and spanish languages 
services on march 16 the source said the agency did not yet plan to 
use the system on its main italian language service 
the agency shut down for two days in february 1987 after 
noneditorial employees struck over plans to introduce computer 
terminals in the newsroom 
</TEXT>
