<DOCNO> AP890309-0010 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
novelist el doctorow wondered what he did 
wrong to deserve a state writing honor and fellow award winner 
robert creeley said he was glad he decided to become a poet instead 
of a veterinarian 
doctorow got the edith wharton citation of merit and creeley 
received the walt whitman citation of merit at a ceremony wednesday 
the new york state writers institute presented the awards which 
are given every two years and carry a 10000 stipend doctorow and 
creeley also will give two annual readings in the next two years in 
the state 
doctorow said he was gratified to be declared a new state 
resource but wondered what i have done wrong to deserve it 
such honors from official sources dont sit well with writers 
who prefer to be somewhere between the state bird and the 
blasphemer with a price on his head doctorow said 
creeley said he once wanted to be a veterinarian because i 
thought animals wouldnt mind my ineptitude as would people but a 
tune in my head from which words later flowed drew him to 
writing said creeley 
doctorows books include the just published billy bathgate 
and worlds fair winner of the 1986 national book award his 
novel ragtime winner of the 1976 national book critics circle 
award was acclaimed for its blending of real people such as harry 
houdini and sigmund freud with doctorows own characters 
creeleys awards include two guggenheim fellowships and the 
robert frost medal given by the poetry society of america creeley 
is one of the founders of the black mountain school of poetry which 
uses sparse language and natural speech rhythms 
the awards instituted two years ago are named for early 20th 
century novelist wharton whose fiction revealed the hypocrisies of 
new york city society and the 19th century poet whitman a long 
island native 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
angela lansbury who recently agreed to stay 
for another year on cbs highest rated show murder she wrote 
has been named woman of the year by the hollywood radio amp television 
society 
she will be honored at the societys 29th international 
broadcasting awards presentation dinner an estimated 1500 
advertising and broadcasting executives are expected at the march 22 
dinner to name the best television and radio commercials of 1988 
miss lansbury won an oscar nomination as best supporting actress 
in her film in gaslight in 1944 she won tony awards for 
broadway productions of mame dear world gypsy and 
sweeney todd 
