although the case could be resolved without altering the courts 
1973 landmark decision missouri authorities and the bush 
administration are urging the court to reconsider its 16yearold 
ruling in a case called roe vs wade 
justice department lawyers have asked the court to let state 
legislatures decide what legal protections if any should be given 
to women seeking abortions 
the courts 1973 decision said women have a constitutional right 
to seek abortions and greatly limited governmental authority to 
interfere with that right 
</TEXT>
