the defendant cannot hijack an airplane then come into a 
courtroom in this country and say well someone told me to do it 
and its alright she said 
the hijackers were trying to deliver a political message the 
prosecutor told the jury 
you can send a message to that hijacker she said 
younis 30 has pleaded innocent in the case considered a test 
of a 1984 statute asserting longarm jurisdiction for the united 
states over the taking of american hostages abroad 
the prosecution suffered a blow earlier in the day as us 
district judge aubrey e robinson jr blocked testimony from a 
government lawyer seeking to rebut the defendants claim he was just 
