the wife of gov michael dukakis also said she had a drinking 
problem long before encountering the stresses of her husbands 
public life and she added i dont blame the presidential 
campaign for my being an alcoholic 
mrs dukakis 52 spoke at a news conference two days after 
completing a monthlong rehabilitation program at edgehill newport 
in rhode island 
she said her drinking became a serious problem in the three 
terribly painful and lonely months after her husbands defeat 
any crisis could have led to the drinking she said the 
campaign was a very positive experience the only problem is that we 
lost 
her husband said i will do whatever is most helpful to her 
accompanying mrs dukakis were her husband and her father harry 
ellis dickson retired associate conductor of the boston pops 
trembling slightly and wearing a smile that appeared forced at 
first mrs dukakis read a statement thanking the thousands of 
people from around the world many of them recovering alcoholics 
who wrote with encouraging words 
she said she would have preferred to keep her crisis private but 
added my hope is that by being public i might encourage others 
to seek help through programs like the one i entered at edgehill 
newport and the extraordinary fellowship of aa 
offshoots of aa such as alanon are also available for family 
and friends of alcoholics asked if the family would get such help 
she said were all going to be part of the program 
mrs dukakis said she was ready to resume her speaking career and 
noted she would continue working on a book 
mrs dukakis conquered a 26year addiction to diet pills in 1982 
but friends said they knew her only as a social drinker who took an 
occasional glass of wine 
earlier mrs dukakis responded to letters from wellwishers with 
a letter of her own on the front page of thursdays usa today 
i have always believed that every experience we have in life 
provides an opportunity for growth and learning she wrote the 
thousands of letters i received from you contributed to my growth 
and i have drawn strength from all that you have shared with me 
