the nations orange harvest for the 198889 
crop season is estimated at 2109 million boxes down 2 percent from 
last months forecast but 5 percent more than produced last season 
the agriculture department said thursday 
florida production based on march 1 indications was estimated 
at 146 million boxes down 3 percent from the february forecast but 
6 percent more than in 198788 
the california harvest was estimated at 61 million boxes 
unchanged from last month and 4 percent more than last season the 
arizona estimate which was carried forward from earlier was put at 
2 million boxes up 10 percent from last season 
texas orange production was forecast at 19 million boxes up 3 
percent from february indications and up 33 percent from last year 
