<TEXT>
a hospital is seeking a new breed of blood donors 
dogs and cats to help set up a blood bank for pets 
special liquids will replace the usual orange juice chasers and 
not all of the donors are expected to sit quietly as they give the 
gift of life but in many respects the blood drive beginning april 2 
will resemble its human counterpart dr alicia faggella a 
veterinarian with the angell memorial animal hospital said thursday 
the blood drive overseen by the massachusetts society for the 
prevention of cruelty to animals will enable the creation of a 
blood bank at the hospital which gave more than 300 lifesaving 
transfusions to dogs and cats last year 
i have not heard of any drives that have been conducted in any 
part of the country so theyre plowing some new ground said dr 
john albers executive director of the american animal hospital 
association in denver its a neat idea 
currently veterinarians keep a few animals in their clinics as 
mascots and blood donors or rely on a network of former patients 
that can be called in he said 
the angell hospital currently has workers bring in their pets for 
regular donations faggella said hospital officials hope to expand 
that to a more formal bloodstorage system that would operate like a 
human blood bank 
plasma would be separated from the blood and frozen making it 
last longer and more types of blood would be on hand faggella 
said like humans animals have different blood types and cat blood 
is different from dog blood 
accidents are the most common reason pets need blood but it also 
is used in treating such diseases as feline leukemia she said 
people really dont realize that our expertise is very similar 
in many instances to human medicine she said we treat pets 
with cancer we do total hip replacements we have animals who have 
diabetes we do cardiovascular heart surgery to repair different 
defects in the heart theres a specialist in every area 
dogs usually are willing to cooperate in donating a pint said 
faggella cats a extra persuasion to donate the usual amount of 
about 3 tablespoons we do tranquilize them so they dont get 
stressed out she said 
so far a few pet owners have registered for the drive 
i think they will be interested in it she said i know we 
have several clients who in the past when blood was very scarce 
theyve been very thankful that their animals have been saved by 
it 
