peru for example eradicated more than 5130 hectares of coca 
plants used to make cocaine over a fourmonth period quayle said 
he also said the bush administration will look into a number of 
policy options that would allow us to do more to reinforce the 
antinarcotics efforts in peru and other andean countries 
the us drug enforcement administration already has agents 
stationed in south america to assist in antidrug efforts they 
gather intelligence assist local police and help in drug 
eradication 
at the same time that we work with other nations we must also 
recognize that we have become a drugsource nation ourselves about 
a quarter of the marijuana consumed in this country is domestically 
grown and a large number of drugs are illegally produced in 
clandestine laboratories in this country he said 
the vice president said there is no reason for a feeling of 
gloom that seems to envelop this issue like a thick clammy fog 
because although the situation is serious the war against drugs is 
winnable 
he cited drug use surveys by the national high school senior 
survey that show drug use among that group at its lowest level since 
the survey began in 1975 
in other words the pessimists are being proven wrong once 
again the american demand for drugs is not insatiable the american 
people are not incapable of selfcontrol 
