george schweitzer a spokesman for cbs inc said those we 
compete with and are in the same business are free to think of any 
competitive situation they want they are free to grow their 
business and we are not 
under terms of a 9yearold court consent decree due to expire 
next year the television networks may produce no more than five 
hours of their own primetime entertainment programming 
even at that the networks have shown little inclination to 
produce their own shows abcs moonlighting was recently placed 
on hiatus but the other two networks have none of their own shows 
on their primetime schedules 
separately the networks are prohibited from having a financial 
interest in other shows they run or sharing in the proceeds from the 
syndication of network shows for reruns under terms of federal 
communications commission rules adopted nearly 20 years ago 
in addition there are rules that prohibit networks from 
packaging their own programs with programs others produce and 
selling them here or abroad 
the networks and hollywood studios have been negotiating 
privately for months on reaching a compromise on the issue of 
federal regulation of networks 
the networks argue that their dominance of the television market 
has slipped since the fcc rules were enacted 
as of last november the three networks share of the primetime 
audience fell to 68 percent from 92 percent in the 197879 season 
