emhart corps board of directors rejected 
an investment groups unsolicited 24 billion takeover offer 
thursday and the company said it had received rival buyout bids from 
other parties 
peter l scott emharts chairman and chief executive officer 
recommended shareholders not tender any of their stock to topper 
