restructuring effort which began in 1986 and four recent 
acquisitions 
the board believes that the full benefits of the companys 
strategies have yet to be realized and that emhart is in a position 
to continue to build on the favorable results achieved over the past 
two years scott said 
accordingly the board does not believe that now is an 
opportune time to sell the company he said 
emharts products include lawn and garden equipment hardware and 
materials used to make footwear 
topper has filed a lawsuit in us district court in richmond 
va to block the use of emharts poison pill antitakeover 
defense emhart has countersued and scott said the company would 
amend the plan to eliminate a provision challenged by topper 
