its hostile 55 billion bid for consolidated gold fields plc 
thursday after gold fields sent shareholders a document detailing 
the companys strengths and future plans 
however the analysts saw little in the document which contained 
numerous valuations and forecasts for gold fields various 
businesses that would cause them to change their own estimates of 
what the british mining company was worth 
south africancontrolled minorco which already owns 296 percent 
of gold fields shares has offered 2050 pounds or 3526 in cash 
and one new minorco share for every two gold fields shares 
minorco shares traded thursday afternoon at 804 pench each down 
9 pence on the day meaning the offer values each gold fields share 
at 1427 pounds however gold fields stock closed above that level 
rising 7 pence to 1430 pounds 
