pratt amp whitney customers once had 
about as much chance of communicating with management as they had of 
hearing a whisper over the roar of its jet engines 
not anymore the company says 
the result is that already this year pratt amp whitney has 
received 32 billion in commercial jet engine orders compared with 
5 billion for all of last year when the company nearly tripled its 
orders vs the year before 
we got our act together but were not satisfied said selwyn 
d berson head of the commercial division at pratt amp whitney a 
subsidiary of united technologies corp 
were going to be the best thats our goal berson said 
during an interview at his office in the companys sprawling east 
hartford headquarters 
sweetened customer relations is part of a general improvement at 
pratt amp whitneys commercial division historically one of the 
pioneers in aircraft engine manufacturing and the biggest in the 
business through the 1960s 
pratt amp whitney also has started a quality improvement drive put 
new manufacturing technology in place and cut expenses by 
eliminating 2000 jobs 
just as important these changes coincide with a broad move by 
airlines worldwide to replace aging jets and expand their fleets for 
a growing number of passengers said mark bobbi an analyst at 
forecast international a consulting firm in newtown conn 
international air traffic has been increasing about 8 percent a 
year while traffic on north american routes has been increasing 
about 4 percent a year bobbi said 
in cumulative book orders pratt amp whitney is behind general 
electric but theyre closing the gap bobbi said 
besides general electric co pratt amp whitneys chief competitors 
for commercial engine sales are rollsroyce ltd and cfm a joint 
venture of ge and snecma of france 
ges commercial engine orders totaled about 23 billion last 
year while cfms orders totaled 5 billion this year ge 
rollsroyce and cfm have combined sales of about 23 billion but 
rollsroyce accounts for only about 500 million of that total 
on the military side pratt amp whitney has bested ge in air force 
engine competition pratt amp whitneys latest victory was winning 60 
percent of a contract announced in february an order worth an 
estimated 350 million 
orders arent counted as sales until the engines are delivered a 
time lag that ranges from two to three years 
the numbers for this year and 1988 markedly differ from 1987 
when pratt amp whitneys shrinking sales were widely publicized the 
low point of that year came when japan airlines announced it was 
dropping pratt amp whitney in favor of ge the airlines decision 
stemmed partly from what it called pratt amp whitneys failure to 
adequately back up sales with service 
the criticism stung company officials who began a 2 million 
twoyear advertising campaign in 1988 aimed at publicizing 
improvement efforts and promising higher responsiveness to customers 
we always believed we were doing a great job out there but 
perception is what counts there was a perception out there that we 
werent really providing the best customer service berson said 
the effort has changed pratt amp whitneys corporate culture 
shifting away from the strictly technical side of building jet 
engines he said 
for example berson said the company now has more than 200 field 
representatives who work daily with airline maintenance crews and 
are empowered to make quick decisions without consulting with 
headquarters first 
the company also established 40 computer centers to give the 
field representatives direct access to corporate headquarters in 
east hartford 
in related step pratt amp whitney has set out to improve its 
record for delivering spare parts which can take up to two years to 
manufacture customers had criticized parts delivery even though 
pratt amp whitney led the industry by delivering parts on schedule 93 
percent of the time berson said 
it didnt matter that it was 93 percent or 94 percent what 
mattered was were we causing the customer some grief work stoppage 
thats a grief if a guy has to stop working on an engine while hes 
waiting for a part that were late on then were causing him 
grief berson said 
bobbi said another key to pratt amp whitneys success is a 
reduction of costs in building engines 
two years ago ges pretax profit margin on aircraft engine sales 
totaled about 16 percent double pratt amp whitneys bobbi said pratt 
amp whitney has just about closed that gap partly because of 
costcutting 
company officials hope the changes will enable pratt amp whitney to 
increase sales the company had been the largest jet engine company 
and had 100 percent of the market until 1970 ge is now regarded as 
the biggest jet engine maker 
berson estimates theres a worldwide market of about 100 billion 
for commercial jet engines and spare parts between now and the year 
2000 with 60 percent of that market composed of widebody airline 
sales 
up to 700 new airliners will be ordered this year and possibly 
the same number next year bobbi said after that anywhere between 
500 to 600 will be ordered annually until 1995 bobbi said 
since many will be widebody jets the future looks good for 
pratt amp whitney widebody engine orders have been a growing segment 
of pratt amp whitney business since the early 1980s the company 
captured about 50 percent of the widebody jet engine orders in 
1988 just ahead of ge industry figures indicate but for pratt amp 
whitney thats no reason to gloat 
by my own measure i think were about even up berson said 
number one they are formidable i never underestimate them i 
never think theyre down and out or anything like that even if i 
have a good day tomorrow they could come right back and rap me in 
the nose 
